	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- Right now, I didn't any deep debugging or tracing to figure what's going on. Anyway, here's the scenery: register 4011 is being written, even if the game doesn't use RAW DMC. This way, the value written is being sent to the DAC, causing the wave to generate an high value, or a "pop" during the playback. If I don't send such write to the DAC, the output is perfect, but games that uses RAW DMC doesn't play, like Battletoads.
<br />
<br />- What am I missing???

		

		</td>
	</tr>
